cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.MA, cs.SY

The paper discusses the potential of multihop cellular networks (MCNs) to provide high bandwidth multimedia services in extended areas with homogeneous quality of service levels. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) as well as information theory (cs.IT) since the paper discusses the signal attenuation with distance and the effect of surrounding obstacles. The paper also mentions multimedia services (cs.MM) and mobile relays (cs.MA) which are relevant sub-categories. Finally, the integration of cellular and ad hoc networking technologies can be considered a system-level approach (cs.SY).
